466 void MCAsmStreamer::addExplicitComment(const Twine &T) { 0
467 StringRef c = T.getSingleStringRef(); 0
468 if (c.equals(StringRef(MAI->getSeparatorString()))) 0
469 return; 0
470 if (c.startswith(StringRef("//"))) { 0
471 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append("\t"); 0
472 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append(MAI->getCommentString()); 0
473 // drop // ----
474 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append(c.slice(2, c.size()).str()); 0
475 } else if (c.startswith(StringRef("/*"))) { 0
476 size_t p = 2, len = c.size() - 2; 0
477 // emit each line in comment as separate newline. ----
478 do { ----
479 size_t newp = std::min(len, c.find_first_of("\r\n", p)); 0
480 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append("\t"); 0
481 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append(MAI->getCommentString()); 0
482 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append(c.slice(p, newp).str()); 0
483 // If we have another line in this comment add line ----
484 if (newp < len) 0
485 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append("\n"); 0
486 p = newp + 1; 0
487 } while (p < len); 0
488 } else if (c.startswith(StringRef(MAI->getCommentString()))) { 0
489 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append("\t"); 0
490 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append(c.str()); 0
491 } else if (c.front() == '#') { 0
492 ----
493 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append("\t"); 0
494 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append(MAI->getCommentString()); 0
495 ExplicitCommentToEmit.append(c.slice(1, c.size()).str()); 0
496 } else ----
497 assert(false && "Unexpected Assembly Comment"); 0
498 // full line comments immediately output ----
499 if (c.back() == '\n') 0
500 emitExplicitComments(); 0
501 } ----

505 if (!Comments.empty()) 286 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
506 OS << Comments; 0

508 } 286 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

937 void MCAsmStreamer::emitXCOFFRenameDirective(const MCSymbol *Name, 0

970 ----
971 void MCAsmStreamer::emitXCOFFCInfoSym(StringRef Name, StringRef Metadata) { 0
972 const char InfoDirective[] = "\t.info "; 0
973 const char *Separator = ", "; 0
974 constexpr int WordSize = sizeof(uint32_t); 0
975 ----
976 // Start by emitting the .info pseudo-op and C_INFO symbol name. ----
977 OS << InfoDirective; 0
978 PrintQuotedString(Name, OS); 0
979 OS << Separator; 0
980 ----
981 size_t MetadataSize = Metadata.size(); 0
982 ----
983 // Emit the 4-byte length of the metadata. ----
984 OS << format_hex(MetadataSize, 10) << Separator; 0
985 ----
986 // Nothing left to do if there's no metadata. ----
987 if (MetadataSize == 0) { 0
988 EmitEOL(); 0
989 return; 0
990 } ----
991 ----
992 // Metadata needs to be padded out to an even word size when generating ----
993 // assembly because the .info pseudo-op can only generate words of data. We ----
994 // apply the same restriction to the object case for consistency, however the ----
995 // linker doesn't require padding, so it will only save bytes specified by the ----
996 // length and discard any padding. ----
997 uint32_t PaddedSize = alignTo(MetadataSize, WordSize); 0
998 uint32_t PaddingSize = PaddedSize - MetadataSize; 0
999 ----
1000 // Write out the payload a word at a time. ----
1001 // ----
1002 // The assembler has a limit on the number of operands in an expression, ----
1003 // so we need multiple .info pseudo-ops. We choose a small number of words ----
1004 // per pseudo-op to keep the assembly readable. ----
1005 constexpr int WordsPerDirective = 5; 0
1006 // Force emitting a new directive to keep the first directive purely about the ----
1007 // name and size of the note. ----
1008 int WordsBeforeNextDirective = 0; 0
1009 auto PrintWord = [&](const uint8_t *WordPtr) { 0
1010 if (WordsBeforeNextDirective-- == 0) { 0
1011 EmitEOL(); 0
1012 OS << InfoDirective; 0
1013 WordsBeforeNextDirective = WordsPerDirective; 0
1014 } ----
1015 OS << Separator; 0
1016 uint32_t Word = llvm::support::endian::read32be(WordPtr); 0
1017 OS << format_hex(Word, 10); 0
1018 }; 0
1019 ----
1020 size_t Index = 0; 0
1021 for (; Index + WordSize <= MetadataSize; Index += WordSize) 0
1022 PrintWord(reinterpret_cast(Metadata.data()) + Index); 0
1023 ----
1024 // If there is padding, then we have at least one byte of payload left ----
1025 // to emit. ----
1026 if (PaddingSize) { 0
1027 assert(PaddedSize - Index == WordSize); 0
1028 std::array LastWord = {0}; 0
1029 ::memcpy(LastWord.data(), Metadata.data() + Index, MetadataSize - Index); 0
1030 PrintWord(LastWord.data()); 0

1146 static void PrintByteList(StringRef Data, raw_ostream &OS, 0
1147 MCAsmInfo::AsmCharLiteralSyntax ACLS) { ----
1148 assert(!Data.empty() && "Cannot generate an empty list."); 0
1149 const auto printCharacterInOctal = [&OS](unsigned char C) { 0
1150 OS << '0'; 0
1151 OS << toOctal(C >> 6); 0
1152 OS << toOctal(C >> 3); 0
1153 OS << toOctal(C >> 0); 0
1154 }; 0
1155 const auto printOneCharacterFor = [printCharacterInOctal]( 0
1156 auto printOnePrintingCharacter) { ----
1157 return [printCharacterInOctal, printOnePrintingCharacter](unsigned char C) { 0
1158 if (isPrint(C)) { 0
1159 printOnePrintingCharacter(static_cast(C)); 0
1160 return; 0
1161 } ----
1162 printCharacterInOctal(C); 0
1163 }; 0
1164 }; 0
1165 const auto printCharacterList = [Data, &OS](const auto &printOneCharacter) { 0
1166 const auto BeginPtr = Data.begin(), EndPtr = Data.end(); 0
1167 for (const unsigned char C : make_range(BeginPtr, EndPtr - 1)) { 0
1168 printOneCharacter(C); 0
1169 OS << ','; 0
1170 } ----
1171 printOneCharacter(*(EndPtr - 1)); 0
1172 }; 0
1173 switch (ACLS) { 0
1174 case MCAsmInfo::ACLS_Unknown: 0
1175 printCharacterList(printCharacterInOctal); 0
1176 return; 0
1177 case MCAsmInfo::ACLS_SingleQuotePrefix: 0
1178 printCharacterList(printOneCharacterFor([&OS](char C) { 0
1179 const char AsmCharLitBuf[2] = {'\'', C}; 0
1180 OS << StringRef(AsmCharLitBuf, sizeof(AsmCharLitBuf)); 0
1181 })); 0
1182 return; 0
1183 } ----
1184 llvm_unreachable("Invalid AsmCharLiteralSyntax value!"); 0
1185 } ----

1297 void MCAsmStreamer::emitBinaryData(StringRef Data) { 0
1298 // This is binary data. Print it in a grid of hex bytes for readability. ----
1299 const size_t Cols = 4; 0
1300 for (size_t I = 0, EI = alignTo(Data.size(), Cols); I < EI; I += Cols) { 0
1301 size_t J = I, EJ = std::min(I + Cols, Data.size()); 0
1302 assert(EJ > 0); 0

1324 void MCAsmStreamer::emitValueImpl(const MCExpr *Value, unsigned Size, 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1325 SMLoc Loc) { ----
1326 assert(Size <= 8 && "Invalid size"); 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1327 assert(getCurrentSectionOnly() && 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1328 "Cannot emit contents before setting section!"); ----
1329 const char *Directive = nullptr; 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1330 switch (Size) { 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1331 default: break; 0
1332 case 1: Directive = MAI->getData8bitsDirective(); break; 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1333 case 2: Directive = MAI->getData16bitsDirective(); break; 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1334 case 4: Directive = MAI->getData32bitsDirective(); break; 22 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1335 case 8: Directive = MAI->getData64bitsDirective(); break; 0
1336 } ----
1337 ----
1338 if (!Directive) { 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1339 int64_t IntValue; ----
1340 if (!Value->evaluateAsAbsolute(IntValue)) 0
1341 report_fatal_error("Don't know how to emit this value."); 0
1342 ----
1343 // We couldn't handle the requested integer size so we fallback by breaking ----
1344 // the request down into several, smaller, integers. ----
1345 // Since sizes greater or equal to "Size" are invalid, we use the greatest ----
1346 // power of 2 that is less than "Size" as our largest piece of granularity. ----
1347 bool IsLittleEndian = MAI->isLittleEndian(); 0
1348 for (unsigned Emitted = 0; Emitted != Size;) { 0
1349 unsigned Remaining = Size - Emitted; 0
1350 // The size of our partial emission must be a power of two less than ----
1351 // Size. ----
1352 unsigned EmissionSize = llvm::bit_floor(std::min(Remaining, Size - 1)); 0
1353 // Calculate the byte offset of our partial emission taking into account ----
1354 // the endianness of the target. ----
1355 unsigned ByteOffset = 0
1356 IsLittleEndian ? Emitted : (Remaining - EmissionSize); 0
1357 uint64_t ValueToEmit = IntValue >> (ByteOffset * 8); 0
1358 // We truncate our partial emission to fit within the bounds of the ----
1359 // emission domain. This produces nicer output and silences potential ----
1360 // truncation warnings when round tripping through another assembler. ----
1361 uint64_t Shift = 64 - EmissionSize * 8; 0
1362 assert(Shift < static_cast( 0
1363 std::numeric_limits::digits) && ----
1364 "undefined behavior"); ----
1365 ValueToEmit &= ~0ULL >> Shift; 0
1366 emitIntValue(ValueToEmit, EmissionSize); 0
1367 Emitted += EmissionSize; 0
1368 } ----
1369 return; 0
1370 } ----
1371 ----
1372 assert(Directive && "Invalid size for machine code value!"); 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1373 OS << Directive; 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1374 if (MCTargetStreamer *TS = getTargetStreamer()) { 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1375 TS->emitValue(Value); 55 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1376 } else { ----
1377 Value->print(OS, MAI); 0
1378 EmitEOL(); 0
1379 } ----
1380 } ----
